The importance of side stones often gets overlooked, but they can really change the appeal of an engagement ring 💍 Here you're looking at two emeralds; the left is set with trapezoids, the right is set with tapered baguettes 💎 The trapezoids add width to the ring and make it feel larger overall, where the baguettes are a delicate accent that really allow the center stone to be the ⭐️ Both beautiful but totally different looks! The trapezoids are a good way to make a smaller center stone appear larger (not the issue here 😋). The baguettes are great for someone who wants a traditional ring with something alittle bit more than just a solid platinum band.
